<SUMMARY>
A linear utility model capturing responder behavior determined by absolute monetary self-interest and opponent envy. Participants gain utility proportional to their own monetary payoffs (scaled by alpha) and experience negative utility directly proportional to absolute monetary payoffs awarded to their opponent (scaled by beta_envy). This explicitly tests whether responders systematically penalize high absolute opponent payoffs independently of proportional fairness or equality.
</SUMMARY>

